üöÄüåô Alotta Money made cryptoart before NFTs.

His earliest works featured:
‚ñ∂Ô∏ègraphic designs for crypto twitter
‚ñ∂Ô∏èimages for crypto-themed merch
‚ñ∂Ô∏èmemes, memes & more memes!

Here‚Äôs how his cryptoart career began
üßµ‚¨áÔ∏è

On September 5, 2017 Alotta Money first purchased crypto. One week later he created his first crypto-themed artwork.

A meme!

He added a QR code so fans could reward his efforts by sending him bitcoin.
Over the next two months, he created promotional material for Vertcoin as well as a faux Crypto Almanac featuring $DOGE

He opened an online shop with Redbubble, displaying his crypto-themed designs on clothing, coffee mugs, and stationary!

Two of his first graphics included:
üöÄ "Rekt‚Äù
üåô ‚ÄúTo the Moon‚Äù

Sensing opportunity, in 2018 he began to market his graphic design services more widely.

He reached out to @czbinance with a customized trailer for the Wolf of Wallstreet and received a response from the Binance CEO!
He built a website to showcase his graphic design skills, which he named the Crypto Pixel Factory!
From 2018-19 he created personalized twitter headers on commission. Business boomed, and he made more than 50 banners!
In March of 2019, he released Miners vs Banks, a physical work of CryptoArt. Signed and numbered, these works were printed on 12" metal discs.
In July of 2019, he created his first augmented reality works with the @ArtiviveApp which included a striking transformation of the US one dollar bill.

In August of 2019, Alotta Money minted his first cryptoart NFT, Empire Crumbles. 

He would go on to tokenize many of the crypto memes, graphics, and twitter headers he created over the past two years.

And we are grateful that he never looked back! üöÄüåô
